# DFIR Analysis

[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)

## Overview
Collection of tools, scripts, and analysis for **Digital Forensics & Incident Response (DFIR)**. 

This repository demonstrates practical skills in memory analysis, artifact parsing, election forensics, and cybersecurity investigations.

### Featured Case Study
**Digital Forensics & Cybersecurity Analysis of Oru West State Constituency 2019 Election**  
*(Forms EC8C & EC8E obtained via FOI request)*

**BSc Cyber Security Case Study**  
National Open University of Nigeria (NOUN)

**Focus Areas:**
- Data integrity verification between EC8C (LGA collation) and EC8E (declaration of result)
- Chain of custody documentation
- Metadata analysis on scanned forms
- Electoral cybersecurity risks in Nigeria’s manual collation process

### Key Capabilities
- Memory forensics and dump analysis
- System artifact parsing and timeline generation
- Election data forensics and anomaly detection
- Custom Python scripts for DFIR workflows

### Technologies
- **Python 3**
- Volatility (or equivalent memory forensics tools)
- Pandas / NumPy for data analysis
- Git for version control

### Repository Structure (Planned)
### For Recruiters, Employers & Visa Applications
This portfolio demonstrates **hands-on Digital Forensics and Incident Response (DFIR)** skills through a real-world Nigerian election forensics case study conducted as part of my BSc Cyber Security program at the National Open University of Nigeria (NOUN).

It highlights my ability to:
- Verify data integrity between election collation forms (EC8C and EC8E)
- Review chain of custody and documentation processes
- Perform metadata analysis on official documents
- Assess cybersecurity and procedural risks in Nigeria’s manual election collation system

